NLRP3 inflammasome-induced neuroinflammation plays a pivotal role in the development of ICH (Lin and Mei, 2021). In this study, NLRP3-positive neuron cells in vitro and vivo were elevated by Hb or hematoma (Fig. 5
                        a, 5b and 5c). NLRP3 trended toward higher expression levels in Hb group and ICH group (Fig. 5d, Fig. 5e, Fig. 5f, Fig. 5g, Fig. S3c and Fig. S4). EGCG, EGCG-CQDs and MCC950 decreased the positive cells and expression significantly in vitro (Fig. 5). Furthermore, we detected factors related to NLRP3 inflammasome (Fig. 6
                        ). Tunel-positive primary cortical cells, or Caspase-1- and Tunel-positive neuronal cells in the perihematomal tissues were upregulated significantly after ICH (Fig. 6a, Fig. 6b and Fig. 6c). NF-κB and its chaperone IκBα increased the synthesis of NLRP3 and facilitated the activation of NLRP3 inflammasome (Afonina et al., 2017). The expression of NF-κB p-p65 and p-IκBα were boosted in Hb and ICH group (Fig. 6d, Fig. 6e, Fig. 6f, Fig. 6g, Fig. S3c and Fig. S4). Caspase-1, the effector of NLRP3 inflammasome, and GSDMD showed the similar results after the insults. EGCG-CQDs, like MCC950, could reduce the expression of these NLRP3 inflammasome-related factors, conversely, EGCG didn’t exert a remarkable impact on these in vivo (Fig. 6d, 6e, 6f and 6 g). The provoked pro-inflammatory cytokines IL-1β and IL-18, and the further promoted factors IL-6 and TNF-α were minimized only by EGCG-CQDs (Fig. 6h). Besides, other inflammatory pathways were also suppressed by EGCG-CQDs strongly in vitro and vivo, such as TLR4/TRAF6 and Caspasse-3/BAX pathway (Fig. S5).
